                        "content": "Which best describes the purpose of behavioral therapy?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe purpose of behavioral therapy is to create effective changes in behavior. Developing structure and organizing time describe aspects of milieu management. Insight is a useful outcome of psychotherapy but does not always result in behavioral change. Relaxation training is a treatment modality effective for reducing stress.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Mental Health\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Stress and Coping, Mood and Affect\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, behavioral therapy, and think about what it entails; this will direct you to the correct option. Also note the word behavioral in the question and correct option.",
                        "id": "184ed08c47884fb4ba8da68635ab9df3",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "27a488c661584b1dbe96e4fb34de2801",
                                "content": " Inform the yelling client that she must leave the group."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "f94180db301a40bfb982cd25eb684f85",
                                "content": "Call security personnel to come to the group therapy session."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "ee3ab03492c8498191f47058dfe8263e",
                                "content": "Explore the other client's responses to the woman's yelling behavior."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "48a36ac0e2c54c8ba359cb8a5a722418",
                                "content": "Firmly reinforce group rules to the woman, stating that aggressive yelling is not acceptable in the group.\n"
                            }
