                        "content": "Which mental health professional is responsible for the milieu in an inpatient psychiatric setting?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe nurse has primary responsibility for managing the milieu in an inpatient psychiatric setting. The psychiatrist, psychologist, and social worker all contribute to maintaining a therapeutic environment, but it is the nurse who has overall responsibility for management of the unit.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Mental Health\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Professional Identity, Health Care Quality\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, milieu management in the inpatient psychiatric setting, to direct you to the correct option.",
                        "id": "58ea4ce7b2784ad3bd014a79742c3070",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
