                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is planning to formulate a psychotherapy group. Several clients are interested in attending the session. The nurse plans the group, based on which management principle?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "\nRationale:\nThe ideal number of clients in a psychotherapy group ranges from six to 10. Having more than 10 members is not recommended because the group will subdivide, which is counterproductive. Too large a group also can create more opportunities for acting out as opposed to working through issues. None of the other options is necessarily true.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Mental Health\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Leadership, Professional Identity\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the formulation of a psychotherapy group. Knowledge regarding the general guidelines related to establishing a psychotherapy group is required to answer this question.\n ",
                        "id": "a998b8d04f8542f7b0ffe9a849359017",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
