                        "content": "<p>The nurse would plan which goals for the termination stage of group development? Select all that apply.</p>",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "<p>Rationale:</p><p>The stages of group development include the initial stage, the working stage, and the termination stage. During the initial stage, the group members become acquainted with one another, and some structuring of group norms, roles, and responsibilities takes place. During the initial stage, group interaction involves superficial conversation. During the working stage, the real work of the group is accomplished. During the termination stage, the group evaluates the experience and explores members' feelings about the group and the impending separation.</p><p><br></p><p>Client Needs: Psychosocial Integrity</p><p>Clinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions</p><p>Cognitive Ability: Applying</p><p>Content Area: Mental Health</p><p>Integrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning</p><p>Priority Concepts: Collaboration, Communication</p><p>Strategies: Subjec</p><p><br></p><p>Test-Taking Strategy:</p><p>Focus on the subject, the termination stage. Reading each item presented and recalling the stages of group development and the definition of termination will assist you in answering this question.</p><p> </p>",
